      <h2 class='article'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9288' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'míngcí', 'noun')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">名词</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=509' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǔ', 'and')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">与</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9288' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'míngcí', 'noun')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">名词</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1347' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xìng', 'sex / nature / surname / suffix corresponding to -ness')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">性</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9257' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cízǔ', 'phrase')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">词组</a>
        Nouns and Nominal Phrases
      </h2>
      <p>
        In a topic-comment sentence there are two types of comments: nominal and verbal.
        A nominal sentence has a nominal (noun-like) phrase as its comment. 
        Usually this means that a nominal phrase forms the predicate of the sentence.
        In contrast, a verbal sentence has a verbal (verb-like) phrase as its comment.
      </p>
      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="nominal"></a>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9288' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'míngcí', 'noun')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">名词</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1347' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xìng', 'sex / nature / surname / suffix corresponding to -ness')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">性</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9257' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cízǔ', 'phrase')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">词组</a>
        Nominal Phrases
      </h3>
      <p>
        A nominal sentence has the form A B <a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>,
        which is a statement that A is a type of B. For example,
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3220' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shēng', 'to be born / to give birth / to grow')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>生</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3896' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'to know / to be aware')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>知</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'used between a modifier and a word to form a word group')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17149' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhě', 'that / this / it / him / her')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>者</a>，<a href='/word_detail.php?id=584' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shàng', 'above / previous')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>上</a><span class='hl'>也</span><br/>
        Those who are born with the possession of knowledge are the highest class of men.
      </p>
      <p>
        from <a href='/word_detail.php?id=7228' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Lúnyǔ', 'The Analects of Confucius')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">论语</a>
        The Analects of Confucius (see below).
        The topic of this sentence is 
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3220' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shēng', 'to be born / to give birth / to grow')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>生</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3896' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'to know / to be aware')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>知</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'used between a modifier and a word to form a word group')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17149' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhě', 'that / this / it / him / her')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>者</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        In nominal sentences in classical Chinese, depending on the period and author,
        there is often no copula, like 'is' in Enlgish or
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=277' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shì', 'is / are / am / yes / to be')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>是</a>
        in modern Chinese.  The copula is nearly entirely missing in early classical Chinese 
        texts and more commonly encountered in later texts.
        In later texts <a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>
        as a final particle also becomes less common.
      </p>
      <p>
        The negative form for this type of sentence is usually A <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1003' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fēi', 'non- / not- / un-')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">非</a>
        B <a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>. For example,
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <span class='hl'>非</span><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1659' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'gǎn', 'to dare')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">敢</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1149' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'hòu', 'after / later / behind')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">后</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a><br/>
        I did not have the courage to lag behind
      </p>
      <p>
        also from the Analects (see below).  The unstated but implied subject in this example is I.
      </p>
      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="text"></a>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=4724' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'kùn', 'to be sleepy / doze off')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">困</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3924' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xué', 'to study / to learn')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">学</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=7228' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Lúnyǔ', 'The Analects of Confucius')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">论语</a> 16.9）
        Text Analects 16.9
      </h3>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=7226' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Kǒngzi', 'Confucius')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">孔子</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=5110' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yuē', 'to speak / to say')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">曰</a>：「<br/>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3220' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shēng', 'to be born / to give birth / to grow')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>生</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3896' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'to know / to be aware')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>知</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'used between a modifier and a word to form a word group')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17149' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhě', 'that / this / it / him / her')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>者</a>，<a href='/word_detail.php?id=584' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shàng', 'above / previous')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>上</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>；<br/>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3924' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xué', 'to study / to learn')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>学</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3896' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'to know / to be aware')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>知</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'used between a modifier and a word to form a word group')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17149' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhě', 'that / this / it / him / her')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>者</a>，<a href='/word_detail.php?id=11728' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cì', 'second-rate')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>次</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>；<br/>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=4725' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'kùn', 'to be in distress')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>困</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3924' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xué', 'to study / to learn')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>学</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'used between a modifier and a word to form a word group')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a>，<a href='/word_detail.php?id=1632' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yòu', 'again / also')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>又</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=6037' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qícì', 'second position')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>其次</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>。<br/>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=4725' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'kùn', 'to be in distress')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>困</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=502' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bù', 'not / no')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>不</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3924' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xué', 'to study / to learn')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>学</a>，<a href='/word_detail.php?id=1021' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'mín', 'the people / citizen')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>民</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3458' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'sī', 'this')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>斯</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=372' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wèi', 'for / to')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>为</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=581' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'xià', 'bottom')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>下</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8355' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǐ', 'final particle')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>矣</a>！<br/>
        」
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        Confucius said, <br/>
        'Those who are born with the possession of knowledge are the highest class of men. <br/>
        Those who learn, and so, readily, get possession of knowledge, are the next.<br/>
        Those who are have difficulty and yet overcome that in learning, are another class next to these. <br/>
        As to those who are dull and stupid and yet do not learn are the lowest of the people.'<br/>
      </p>
      <p>
        The Analects are the sayings of Confucius recorded by his disciples (c. 479 BCE—221 BCE)
        and is a model of an early classical Chinese writing.
      </p>
      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="text2"></a>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=2618' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'mǎ', 'horse')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">马</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=502' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bù', 'not / no')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">不</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1644' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jìn', 'to advance / to enter')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">进</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=925' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'also')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">也</a>（<a href='/word_detail.php?id=7228' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Lúnyǔ', 'The Analects of Confucius')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">论语</a> 6.13）
        Text Analects 6.13
      </h3>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17151' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǐ', 'a polite form of address / master')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>子</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=5110' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yuē', 'to speak / to say')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>曰</a>、<br/>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=5165' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Mèng', 'Meng')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">孟</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=730' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'him / her / it')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">之</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3541' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fǎn', 'reverse / opposite / wrong side out or up')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">反</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=502' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bù', 'not / no')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">不</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=14566' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fá', 'to cut down / to fell / to attack / to boast')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">伐</a>、<br/>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3988' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bēn', 'to gallop / to hurry or rush / to run quickly / to elope')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">奔</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3708' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'diàn', 'palace hall / ceremonial hall')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">殿</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=1317' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jiāng', 'will, shall (future tense)')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">将</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=916' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'rù', 'to enter')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">入</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2137' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'mén', 'opening / door / gate / doorway / gateway')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">门</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=1380' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cè', 'method / plan / policy / scheme')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">策</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1574' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qí', 'his / her / its / theirs / that')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">其</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2618' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'mǎ', 'horse')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">马</a>、<br/>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=5110' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yuē', 'to speak / to say')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">曰</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=1003' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fēi', 'non- / not- / un-')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>非</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1659' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'gǎn', 'to dare')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>敢</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1149' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'hòu', 'after / later / behind')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>后</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>、<a href='/word_detail.php?id=2618' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'mǎ', 'horse')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>马</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=502' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'bù', 'not / no')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>不</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1644' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jìn', 'to advance / to enter')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>进</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>。<br/>
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        The Master said, <br/>
        'Meng Zhifan does not boast of his merit. <br/>
        Being in the rear on an occasion of flight, when they were about to enter the gate, 
        he whipped up his horse, <br/>
        saying, "It is not that I dare to be last. My horse would not advance."'<br/>
      </p>
      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="questions"></a>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=6446' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yíwèn', 'a question / a query')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>疑问</a>
        Questions
      </h3>
      <p>
        In very early classical texts, such as <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17850' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Zuǒ Zhuàn', 'Zuozhuan / Tsochuan / Zuo\'s commentary')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">左传</a> Zuozhuan the interrogative particle <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3641' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'hū', 'expresses question or doubt')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>乎</a>
        was added after <a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a> 
        to form questions.  Later, the combination <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3641' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'hū', 'expresses question or doubt')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">乎</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a>
        was replaced by <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17903' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yú', 'interrogative particle')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>与</a> or <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17904' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yé', 'interrogative particle')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>邪</a>.  For example,
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17183' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fú', 'now / still')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>夫</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1003' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fēi', 'non- / not- / un-')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>非</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17905' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jìn', 'all / every')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>尽</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=399' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'rén', 'person / people')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>人</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'used between a modifier and a word to form a word group')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3223' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǐ', 'child / son')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>子</a>        <span class='hl'>与</span><br/>
        Are we not all somebody's son?
      </p>
      <p>
        from <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17096' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Mèng Zǐ', 'Mencius')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">孟子</a> 
        Mencius and
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=1574' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'qí', 'his / her / its / theirs / that')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>其</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17906' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhèng', 'true')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>正</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=2482' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'sè', 'color / look / appearance')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>色</a><span class='hl'>邪</span><br/>
        Is this its true color?
      </p>
      <p>
        from <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9741' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Zhuāng Zǐ', 'Zhuang Zi')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">庄子</a> Zhuang Zi.
      </p>
      <p>
        The final particle <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17907' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'fú', 'is it not? / final particle')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>夫</a> means is it not? and is used in a similar way to the 
        modern particle <a href='/word_detail.php?id=4980' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ba', '...right? / ...OK?')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>吧</a>. For example,
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3300' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'rán', 'so / thus')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>然</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1336' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'ér', 'and / as well as / but (not) / yet (not)')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>而</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhì', 'to arrive')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>至</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=624' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cǐ', 'this, these')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>此</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17838' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jí', 'to go to an extreme')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>极</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17165' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhě', 'nominalizing function word')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>者</a>，<a href='/word_detail.php?id=12920' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'mìng', 'fate')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>命</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a><span class='hl'>夫</span><br/>
        Thus I have arrived at this eventuality.  Is it not fate?
      </p>
      <p>
        from <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9741' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Zhuāng Zǐ', 'Zhuang Zi')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">庄子</a> Zhuang Zi.
      </p>
      <h3 class='article'>
        <a name="pronouns"></a>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=9292' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'dàicí', 'pronoun')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">代词</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=509' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǔ', 'and')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">与</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=9275' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhùcí', 'particle')" onmouseout="hideToolTip()">助词</a>
        Pronouns and Particles
      </h3>
      <p>
        A pronoun can be substituted for a noun when using a nominal predicate.  Commonly encountered
        pronouns are <a href='/word_detail.php?id=624' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'cǐ', 'this, these')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>此</a>, <a href='/word_detail.php?id=3458' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'sī', 'this')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>斯</a>, and <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17908' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shì', 'this / that')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>是</a>.  For example,
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <span class='hl'>此</span><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17559' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'Wén', 'Wen')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>文</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=3236' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wáng', 'king / prince')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>王</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=13788' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zhī', 'used between a modifier and a word to form a word group')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>之</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17909' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yǒng', 'courage')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>勇</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a><br/>
        This was King Wen's bravery.
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <span class='hl'>是</span><a href='/word_detail.php?id=5060' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yì', 'also')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>亦</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=1343' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'zǒu', 'to walk / to go / to move / to leave')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>走</a><a href='/word_detail.php?id=8853' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'yě', 'a final modal particle indicating certainy or decision')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>也</a><br/>
        This is also running away.
      </p>
      <p>
        both from Mencius.  In high classical Chinese <a href='/word_detail.php?id=17908' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'shì', 'this / that')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>是</a> was a pronoun rather than a verb as it is in modern 
        Chinese. It aquired this function in the Han Dynasty.
      </p>
      <p>
        The pronoun <a href='/word_detail.php?id=5046' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'jiē', 'all / each and every / in all cases')" 
        onmouseout="hideToolTip()">皆</a> is used when the subject is plural.  For example,
      </p>
      <p class='example'>
        <a href='/word_detail.php?id=5049' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'wŭ yùn', 'five aggregates / five skandhas / five dharmas')" onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>五蕴</a><span class='hl'>皆</span><a href='/word_detail.php?id=17657' onmouseover="showToolTip(this, 'kōng', 'emptiness')" 
        onmouseout='hideToolTip()'>空</a><br/>
        all five skandhas are empty
      </p>
      <p>
        from the Heart Sutra.
      </p>
